4 basic forces

  • Gravity - Only attractive
  • Electromagnetic Force - Attractive and repulsive
    • Means they can bring things together, or push them apart
  • Weak Nuclear Force
  • Strong nuclear force

How to solve

  1. Identify physical principles involved (Draw FBD)
  2. ID what you need to determine. If you're finding acceleration, force, etc.
  3. Somehow use to rearrange and solve. Kinematics equations could be involved too
  4. Sanity Check

Tension and Weight

Definition (Weight).

The force of gravity, which is the force acting on us at all times pulling us down.
Gravity doesn't discriminate

Definition (Tension).

A force along the length of a medium. In a rope, getting pulled on is tension

How do Kinematic Equations get involved?
